OL,3,CMan, 60, admits strangling estranged
OL,4,Cwife at her home with bootlace
OL,6,FMcDaid left the house after committing
OL,7,Fthe fatal act before returning a few
OL,8,Fminutes later to find one of the sons
OL,9,Ftrying to enter and telling him: "You
OL,10,Fcan't go in the house because I've
OL,11,Fkilled her."
OL,13,FThe Nottinghamshire force said McDaid
OL,14,Fhad driven away from the scene while
OL,15,Fcalling the police to say his wife was
OL,16,Fdead and that he was responsible.
OL,18,FA boot with its laces missing was
OL,19,Ffound on a narrow boat McDaid was
OL,20,Fliving on, officers added.
